    • ContentView

      public ContentView​(@Nullable P content)

      Fully-Parameterized Constructor

      Constructs a new ContentView that displays the specified content.

      Details

      1. The primary purpose of a ContentView implementation is to define the actions taken upon a content change.
        1. Refer to TransitionContentView.onContentChange(Pane, Pane) for example usage.
      2. The baseline ContentView contains a property containing the content to be displayed by this ContentView.
      3. Implementing classes provide additional functionality, setup, management, and usage of the content.
      Parameters:
      content - The content to be displayed by this ContentView.
